{
  "texts": [
    "Consequently, universities should formulate explicit policies governing AI tool usage.",
    "Moreover, the ethical and proficient deployment of such technologies mandates AI literacy education for both students and faculty.",
    "This research advocates for a re-evaluation of educational objectives and assessment methods in the AI era, urging a redesign of pedagogical strategies to leverage the potential benefits of AI rather than restrict its use.",
    "The primary limitation of this exploratory study was its restricted sample size from a single institution.",
    "Nonetheless, the mixed-methods approach yielded insightful preliminary data for guiding subsequent inquiries into AI's adoption and its broader effects across diverse student demographics."
  ]
}